               <!--a saint, writer-->
                  <birth notBefore="0329" notAfter="0330"/>
                  <floruit notBefore="0350" notAfter="0379">A  saint and doctor of the church, he was an important figure in the 4th century strife against 
                     Arianism, an organizer of the monastic life and a prolific writer.
                     Excerpts of his works are extant in Ethiopic. 
                     <persName ref="PRS2546Basilth">Basil the Great</persName> came
                     from a deeply Christian Greek family, many members of which are venerated as saints.
                     He visited all of the most important monastic 
                     centres in <placeName ref="LOC5833Syria">Syria</placeName> and <placeName ref="LOC4797Mesopo">Mesopotamia</placeName>, 
